HEADWORD: Antemeridian
<hw>An`te*me*rid"i*an</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>antemeridianus</ets>; <ets>ante</ets> + <ets>meridianus</ets>
belonging to midday or noon. See <er>Meridian</er>.]</ety> <def>Being
before noon; in or pertaining to the forenoon. (Abbrev. <sc>a.
m.</sc>)</def>⟦br⟧
